==English==

===Etymology===
A compound of [[hair]] + [[pin]].  The adjective form recalls the tight bend characteristic of a hairpin.

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ˈheɪrpɪn/}}
*{{audio|en-us-hairpin.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|-}}
#Characterized by an [[abrupt]] or [[extreme]] [[bend]]; shaped like a hairpin.
#:''Drive carefully. That road has a lot of '''hairpin''' turns.''

===Noun===
{{en-noun|sg=[[hair]][[pin]]}}

# A [[pin]] or [[fastener]] for the hair.

